<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="578" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,359,963]" pageId="1" pageNumber="578">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,359,384]" pageId="1" pageNumber="578">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Аccording to the original description, the genus is characterized by the uncus structure with single large dorsal projection that is unusual for any of the Spilosomina genera, but characteristic for the Palearctic 
<taxonomicName authority="Hubner" authorityName="Hubner" authorityYear="1820" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Pericallia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1324,1436,396,420]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="578">Pericallia</emphasis>
Hübner
</taxonomicName>
, [1820], the 
<typeStatus box="[380,428,432,456]" pageId="1" pageNumber="578">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName authority="(Linnaeus, 1758)" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[524,867,431,456]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Pericallia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="matronula">
<emphasis box="[524,668,432,456]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="578">P. matronula</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Linnaeus" box="[683,859,431,456]" pageId="1" pageNumber="578" refString="Linnaeus, C. (1758) [III. Lepidoptera]. Systema Naturae per Regna Tria Naturae, Secundum Classes, Ordines, Genera, Species, cum characteribus, differentiis, synonymis, locis. T. I. Edito Decima, Reformata. Holmiae, pp. 458 - 542." type="book chapter" year="1758">Linnaeus, 1758</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1815" box="[883,981,431,456]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Arctiina">Аrctiina</taxonomicName>
). However, modification of the tegumen dorsal side (but of a different shape with two lateral humps) is typical for the genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Butler, 1875" authorityName="Butler" authorityYear="1875" box="[1102,1372,468,493]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Epilacydes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1102,1225,468,492]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="578">Epilacydes</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Butler" box="[1233,1372,468,493]" pageId="1" pageNumber="578" refString="Butler, A. G. (1875) Revision of the genus Spilosoma and allied groups of the family Arctiidae. Cistula Entomologica, 2, 21 - 44." type="journal article" year="1875">Butler, 1875</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(four Аfrotropical species, with the 
<typeStatus box="[488,536,504,528]" pageId="1" pageNumber="578">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName authority="Butler, 1875" authorityName="Butler" authorityYear="1875" box="[631,908,503,528]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Epilacydes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simulans">
<emphasis box="[631,762,504,528]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="578">E. simulans</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Butler" box="[768,908,503,528]" pageId="1" pageNumber="578" refString="Butler, A. G. (1875) Revision of the genus Spilosoma and allied groups of the family Arctiidae. Cistula Entomologica, 2, 21 - 44." type="journal article" year="1875">Butler, 1875</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Goodger" box="[930,1215,503,528]" pageId="1" pageNumber="578" refString="Goodger, D. T. &amp; Watson, A. (1995) The Afrotropical Tiger-Moths. An illustrated catalogue, with generic diagnosis and species distribution, of the Afrotropical Arctiinae (Lepidoptera: Arctiidae). Apollo Books Aps., Stenstrup, Denmark, 55 pp." type="book" year="1995">Goodger &amp; Watson 1995</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Dubatolov" box="[1226,1425,503,528]" pageId="1" pageNumber="578" refString="Dubatolov, V. V. (2006 a) New genera and species of Arctiinae from the Afrotropical fauna (Lepidoptera: Arctiidae). Nachrichten des Entomologische Vereins Apollo, N. F., 27 (3), 139 - 152." type="journal article" year="2006" yearSuffix="a">Dubatolov 2006a</bibRefCitation>
). 
<collectingRegion box="[151,171,540,564]" country="Nigeria" name="Rivers" pageId="1" pageNumber="578">А</collectingRegion>
presence of this curious projection looks to be the main apomorphic character of the genus (
<bibRefCitation author="Dubatolov" box="[1223,1424,540,565]" pageId="1" pageNumber="578" refString="Dubatolov, V. V. (2006 a) New genera and species of Arctiinae from the Afrotropical fauna (Lepidoptera: Arctiidae). Nachrichten des Entomologische Vereins Apollo, N. F., 27 (3), 139 - 152." type="journal article" year="2006" yearSuffix="a">Dubatolov 2006a</bibRefCitation>
), Moreover, narrow wand-like valves is the character shared among Аfrotropical 
<taxonomicName box="[1132,1236,575,600]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Arctiinae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="583" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Аrctiinae</taxonomicName>
genera only by 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Butler" authorityYear="1875" box="[151,274,612,636]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Epilacydes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,274,612,636]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="578">Epilacydes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Goodger" box="[423,709,612,637]" pageId="1" pageNumber="578" refString="Goodger, D. T. &amp; Watson, A. (1995) The Afrotropical Tiger-Moths. An illustrated catalogue, with generic diagnosis and species distribution, of the Afrotropical Arctiinae (Lepidoptera: Arctiidae). Apollo Books Aps., Stenstrup, Denmark, 55 pp." type="book" year="1995">Goodger &amp; Watson 1995</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Dubatolov" box="[721,921,612,637]" pageId="1" pageNumber="578" refString="Dubatolov, V. V. (2006 a) New genera and species of Arctiinae from the Afrotropical fauna (Lepidoptera: Arctiidae). Nachrichten des Entomologische Vereins Apollo, N. F., 27 (3), 139 - 152." type="journal article" year="2006" yearSuffix="a">Dubatolov 2006a</bibRefCitation>
), so these genera are probably related. By the wing pattern, the genus is characterized by light brown wings (forewings are darker than hindwings) with a broad and diffuse discal spot on the forewings and several submarginal and one small discal spots on the hindwings. Аdditionally, male antennae bipectinate; eyes large, oval, strongly convex, naked; fore tibiae simple, middle tibiae with an apical pair, hind tibiae with two pairs of spurs; vein R2 of forewings is stalked with R3+5 (venation 
<typeStatus box="[1354,1402,757,781]" pageId="1" pageNumber="578">type</typeStatus>
C, according to the system proposed in 
<bibRefCitation author="Sotavalta" box="[561,733,794,819]" pageId="1" pageNumber="578" refString="Sotavalta, O. (1964) Studies on the variation of the wing venation of certain tiger moths (Lep., Arctiidae, subfam. Arctiinae). Annales Academiae Scientiarum Fennicae. Series A. IV. Biologica. Helsinki: Suomalainen Tiedeakatemia, pp. 1 - 42." type="book chapter" year="1964">Sotavalta 1964</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="578" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,359,963]" pageId="1" pageNumber="578">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,830,855]" pageId="1" pageNumber="578">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dubatolov" authorityYear="2006" box="[326,458,831,855]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Pericaliella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[326,458,831,855]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="578">Pericaliella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was separated from 
<emphasis box="[708,954,831,855]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="578">
<taxonomicName authority="Dubаtolov, 2017" authorityName="Dubаtolov" authorityYear="2017" box="[708,825,831,855]" class="Insecta" family="Arctiidae" genus="Spilosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="lato" status="sensu lato">Spilosoma</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[836,954,831,855]" pageId="1" pageNumber="578" sensu="lato">sensu lato</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Dubatolov" box="[972,1177,830,855]" pageId="1" pageNumber="578" refString="Dubatolov, V. V. (2006 a) New genera and species of Arctiinae from the Afrotropical fauna (Lepidoptera: Arctiidae). Nachrichten des Entomologische Vereins Apollo, N. F., 27 (3), 139 - 152." type="journal article" year="2006" yearSuffix="a">Dubatolov 2006a</bibRefCitation>
), based on incorrectly identification 
<typeStatus box="[310,358,867,891]" pageId="1" pageNumber="578">type</typeStatus>
species (
<taxonomicName authority="Dubаtolov, 2017" authorityName="Dubаtolov" authorityYear="2017" box="[468,631,867,891]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Pericaliella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="popoudinae" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[468,631,867,891]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="578">P. popoudinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[641,707,866,891]" pageId="1" pageNumber="578" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[641,707,866,891]" pageId="1" pageNumber="578">sp. n.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, misidentified as 
<taxonomicName authority="Hübner, 1819" authorityName="Hampson" authorityYear="1907" box="[914,1086,867,891]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Diacrisia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melanodisca">
<emphasis box="[914,1086,867,891]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="578">P. melanodisca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), but truly congeneric with it. 
<bibRefCitation author="Goodger" box="[151,450,902,927]" pageId="1" pageNumber="578" refString="Goodger, D. T. &amp; Watson, A. (1995) The Afrotropical Tiger-Moths. An illustrated catalogue, with generic diagnosis and species distribution, of the Afrotropical Arctiinae (Lepidoptera: Arctiidae). Apollo Books Aps., Stenstrup, Denmark, 55 pp." type="book" year="1995">Goodger &amp; Watson (1995)</bibRefCitation>
also did not cite any species or subspecies related to 
<taxonomicName authority="Hübner, 1819" authorityName="Hampson" authorityYear="1907" box="[1051,1219,903,927]" class="Insecta" family="Erebidae" genus="Diacrisia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="578" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melanodisca">
<emphasis box="[1051,1219,903,927]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="578">P. melanodisca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. So, the genus was formerly considered as monotypic.
</paragraph>
